a_0.formal problem:
theorem
fixes x :: real and f :: "real \<Rightarrow> real"
assumes h0 : "\<forall> x. f x = 5 * x - 4"
shows  "f (f (f 2)) = 126"
a_0.formal solution:
(* ### Problem
 If $f(x) = 5x-4$, what is $f(f(f(2)))$? The final Answer is 126
 ### Proof
 We have that \begin{align} f(2) &= 5(2) - 4 = 6, \\ f(f(2)) &= f(6) = 5(6) - 4 = 26, \\ f(f(f(2))) &= f(f(6)) = f(26) = 5(26) - 4 = \boxed{126}. \end{align}
 *)

fixes x :: real and f :: "real \<Rightarrow> real"
